File: 67 more people have died and the Department extended condolences to their loved ones as well as thanks to the health workers who tended to them. JOHANNESBURG - The Department of Health reported 1,767 new cases of COVID-19. The cumulative number of detected cases in the country is 674,339. WATCH: Update on COVID-19 travel regulations A total of 67 more people have died and the department extended condolences to their loved ones as well as thanks to the health workers who tended to them. 4,187,917 tests have been conducted in total with 23,426 new tests conducted since the last report. Recoveries now stand at 608,112 which translates to a recovery rate of 90 percent. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.